    • Method Detail

      • transcribe

        public VectorFunction transcribe(NEATGenotype genotype,
                        VectorFunction function)
        Description copied from class: Transcriber
        Transcribe the given genotype to a phenotype function. If the genotype and function are the same object then implementations should simply return the genotype.
        Specified by:
        transcribe in class Transcriber<NEATGenotype,VectorFunction>
        Parameters:
        genotype - The genotype to transcribe.
        function - Optionally a reference to a previously generated function. This allows the transcriber the option to re-use the function objects it generates in the case that they are large and deallocating and recreating them from scratch is inefficient. Note that this will be null at times (for example in the first calls to this method).
